I am in this category too Zack! I know what my experiences are, I do this
for the love of it, not for anyone else but me.  Once you throw grants and
studies into it, now you have a protocol or rules to follow. It can
seriously limit not only the enjoyment, but the way different people get
their results.



Heather


---------- Original Message ----------
From: Zack Widup &lt;w9sz.zack@...&gt;
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] of EVP &quot;experiments&quot; and Grants
Date: Tue, 5 May 2009 22:22:02 -0500

I think the thing is that there are some of us here (well, at least one and
maybe two) who could care less what the rest of the world thinks. We aren&#39;t
out to prove anything to the world. We&#39;re not intertestid in &quot;studies&quot; or
&quot;grants.&quot; We know what we can get and we just do it for the enjoyment of
hearing the EVP/ITC communication ourselves



I am in this category and I have a feeling Frank is to some extent, too.



Zack.


